We don't have any decent (=10.0dps) single target damage add (especially not in a base line); <br>
We don't have cool RP Skills like speed of sound, or bunker of faith, or group purge; <br>
We don't have a third rezzing class; <br>
We don't have any melee/healing hybrid class;<br>
We don't have any pbaoe spells (xept the very weak Thane one on a timer);<br>
<br>
Yeah, whatever, I guess. As far as I can tell, Realm dominance is dependent almost entirely on server population. On my server, Albion has more peeps, but Midgard is unquestionably dominant. So I guess I have a different perspective on that.<br>
<br>
Every realm can compile a list of things that the other realms get and they don't. And every realm can compile a list of its advantages, too. As for Midgard:<br>
<br>
There is no melee hybrid anywhere that can hold a candle to a Skald. If there was, it would be a Thane. Our primary healing class gets very powerful crowd control and a power regen buff in the same line. Our music class doesn't have to switch instruments or wear a big &quot;Kill Me!&quot; lute into combat. Runemasters are incredibly overloaded with utility spells and abilities, they're like Swiss Army Wizards, and I can not imagine why anyone would play an Eldritch if a Runemaster were available. The superiority of Left Axe provides a distinct advantage to all our dual-wielding classes. Just about every Midgard class can wield 2-handers without even speccing in them; in most other realms, 2-handed weapons are limited to fighter-types and even then they require a long-term spec commitment. In particular, no other realm's Assassins can switch between 1-handers and 2-handers as the situation requires. Damn near everyone in Midgard wears chain. And so on, and so on...<br>
<br>
Look, the myth of Realm Gimpedness is just a myth. I'm sorry, but there it is. It's a paranoid fantasy. Nothing else. The only realm that can possibly complain about essential imbalance is Hibernia, and that's because their Assassin and two of their three tanks are very, very weak. But the third is awesome, so there you go.<br>
<br>
There is only one thing that can really 'gimp' a realm, and that's server population imbalance, and nobody has ever suggested a workable solution for THAT problem. So...I guess I DO feel that we should try to be happy with our incredibly fun and useful class, and at least hold the paranoia down to a minimum.<br>
<br>
